<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/280: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frost</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-29T18:00:00-04:00">March 29, 1938—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 29—5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>38. Referring to my telegram No. 36, March 24, 4 p.m. and to the
                            Department’s 26, March 29, 11 a.m. Treaty Commission approved exchange
                            proposal at meeting on March 25 and expects to reach decision on the
                            general provisions <hi rend="italic">en bloc</hi> at meeting on April
                            1.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>